column5: I cant go ,so there is an opening. Of course,it would be up to the gang to allow you in.  Contact percher or memart.
Don't give us that Bull Brian... honestly.. I'm pretty sure they won't give you much worse of an initiation than we gave Joe this winter!
That's to bad Brian I was looking forward to meeting you.Maybe next time. Dan
Wayne,the two days I had booked were non holiday.Days without pay. So they can say no. Atleast I still have my 3 days of deer.Then thats it.
What    come on you must set your priorities   it's fishing.....fishing  you can work anytime
I'll call his boss and tell him that he's been slandering me using his work computer. That should get him a day or two off !!
Well then you could come.. now couldn't you !
LO  ahhhhh the mermories   good times   good times
memart Sir douG is looking for a boat to go out on.Just give Doug a PM  Brian too bad you can't come this year I was looking forward to meeting you.  MTP
HAHAHAHA!!!... How did I know you were going to wimp out!!!... wimpy wimpy wimpy!!!

And what about you Thin blood has the thought of attending crossed your mind.  Just come down we will fit you with propane heater fed with a hose into your survival suit.  You won't be cold after that.Its only 19 hours drive right?

Yeah, 19-21 hour drive.. have you ever driven that far just to go fishing???... I remember your Salmon fishing report from back in the summer, you made a 6hr. drive sound like an EPIC trip to go fishing... you should drive down to 'Bama sometime and see what a real drive is like!!!  I will not be attending the BOQ G2G this year!
Take the time and money to drive 20 hours north of where you are right now and maybe you'll undersatnd...
